WEBVTT

00:30.730 --> 00:34.866
My daughter will be singing
in the competition tomorrow evening.

00:34.867 --> 00:38.860
- Oh, June Allison.
- Oh, Loretta Young.

00:38.937 --> 00:42.703
Her late father and I
had such high hopes for her.

00:42.774 --> 00:46.540
But she's determined
to try to be a singer.

00:46.612 --> 00:49.809
- I suppose she has
some talent in that area.

00:49.882 --> 00:52.214
It's such a relief you were able
to accommodate us...

00:52.284 --> 00:54.218
by bringing
the dresses here today.

00:54.286 --> 00:56.220
Thank you.

00:56.288 --> 00:59.724
Oh! Mother?
This is it.

01:00.792 --> 01:02.987
The perfect dress.

01:03.061 --> 01:06.292
Mother, it's a beautiful dress.
But it's not for my figure.

01:06.365 --> 01:09.129
A well-made dress works
on any figure.

01:09.201 --> 01:11.635
Certainly, Mother.

01:12.971 --> 01:14.905
You're so willful, Edna.

01:16.108 --> 01:18.576
Just like my sister,
your namesake,

01:18.644 --> 01:22.239
where in her wild youth,
she found herself in the family way.

01:22.314 --> 01:25.249
Your father got her a doctor
and took care of her problem.

01:25.317 --> 01:28.445
She hemorrhaged
and was scarred inside forever.

01:28.520 --> 01:34.015
My mother made me swear I'd name
my first daughter after Edna,

01:34.092 --> 01:38.119
- Who could never bear children
of her own.

01:38.196 --> 01:40.756
Turn around, Edna.

01:40.832 --> 01:43.926
We'll take the dress she has on.

01:46.838 --> 01:51.002
Mother, I can't sing
in a dress that doesn't fit.

01:51.076 --> 01:53.044
Look at it.

01:54.112 --> 01:57.172
The dress fits the occasion.

01:57.249 --> 01:59.274
It's you who doesn't fit.

02:04.990 --> 02:06.924
All right.

02:07.993 --> 02:10.894
♪ ♪

02:14.232 --> 02:17.167
♪ ♪

02:24.476 --> 02:30.381
♪ Said the Blues ain't nothin' ♪

02:30.449 --> 02:35.910
♪ But a woman cryin' for a man ♪

02:35.988 --> 02:39.014
♪ I said the Blues ♪

02:39.091 --> 02:42.720
♪ Ain't nothin' ♪ ♪

02:42.794 --> 02:47.231
- That is such a beautiful song.
It... Sorry.
- Thank you.

02:47.299 --> 02:50.462
- What is it?
- Somethin' I've been
singing all my life.

02:50.535 --> 02:52.526
Spiced up a little.

02:52.604 --> 02:56.165
Boy, it's just, you sing it
like you really mean it.

02:56.241 --> 02:58.505
What are you gonna sing?

02:58.577 --> 03:01.171
Well, I signed up to sing
"You'll Never Walk Alone."

03:02.681 --> 03:06.048
My mother says it's universal.

03:06.118 --> 03:08.552
She says the personal songs
never win.

03:08.620 --> 03:12.420
- They make people dwell on themselves.
- Oh, I don't know about that.

03:12.491 --> 03:15.426
But I do know it's more fun
to sing a song that you like...

03:15.494 --> 03:18.588
than to try to please everybody.

03:18.663 --> 03:21.564
♪ Hey, there ♪

03:21.633 --> 03:25.228
- ♪ You with the stars
in your eyes ♪
- You know that?

03:25.303 --> 03:29.433
- Rosemary Clooney?
- ♪ Love never made
a fool of you ♪

03:29.508 --> 03:32.966
- Yeah.
- ♪ You used to be
two eyes ♪ ♪

03:33.045 --> 03:35.673
I mean, sing a song
that you like.

03:35.747 --> 03:38.614
And you got a stage,
an audience...

03:38.683 --> 03:40.913
and a real pretty dress.

03:40.986 --> 03:44.717
The dress fits the occasion.

03:44.790 --> 03:47.156
It's a real pretty dress.

03:47.225 --> 03:50.160
♪ ♪

03:54.566 --> 03:59.094
♪ When she wants some lovin' ♪

03:59.171 --> 04:05.076
♪ I'm sure all you women
will understand ♪

04:08.180 --> 04:11.946
She'll win.
She deserves it.

04:12.017 --> 04:14.349
♪ Try to keep your man happy ♪

04:14.419 --> 04:20.380
♪ Although you find him
real hard to please ♪

04:20.459 --> 04:24.793
♪ Yeah ♪ ♪

04:24.863 --> 04:28.458
-  Thank you, Miss Shelley.

04:28.533 --> 04:31.161
And coming to the end
of the competing vocalists,

04:31.236 --> 04:36.435
Number Nine,
Edna Buxton from Chestnut Hill.

04:36.508 --> 04:39.443
She'll be singing
"You'll Never Walk Alone."

04:41.513 --> 04:44.846
Uh, Miss Buxton
will be singing...

04:45.917 --> 04:47.976
"Hey There."

04:48.053 --> 04:49.987
"Hey There."

04:50.055 --> 04:53.218
♪ ♪

04:53.291 --> 04:56.158
♪ Hey there ♪

04:56.228 --> 05:01.495
♪ You with the stars
in your eyes ♪

05:01.566 --> 05:07.163
♪ Love never made
a fool of you ♪

05:07.239 --> 05:13.371
♪ You used to be two eyes ♪

05:16.281 --> 05:18.909
♪ Hey there ♪

05:18.984 --> 05:24.923
♪ You on that
high-flying cloud ♪

05:24.990 --> 05:29.723
♪ Though he won't throw
a crumb to you ♪

05:29.794 --> 05:35.824
♪ You think someday
he'll come to you ♪

05:37.435 --> 05:41.667
♪ Better forget him ♪

05:41.740 --> 05:47.508
♪ Him with his nose in the air ♪

05:47.579 --> 05:53.074
♪ He has you dancing
on a string ♪

05:53.151 --> 05:59.681
♪ Break it and he won't care ♪

05:59.758 --> 06:03.922
♪ Won't you take this advice ♪

06:03.995 --> 06:06.361
♪ I offer ♪

06:06.431 --> 06:10.527
♪ Like a mother ♪

06:10.602 --> 06:18.475
♪ Or are you
not seeing things too clear ♪

06:18.543 --> 06:25.039
♪ Are you too much
in love to hear ♪

06:25.116 --> 06:31.646
♪ Is it all going in one ear ♪

06:31.723 --> 06:34.157
♪ And out ♪

06:34.226 --> 06:38.822
♪ The other ♪ ♪

06:52.744 --> 06:54.837
And finally, first prize,

06:54.913 --> 06:58.007
a recording contract
with McMartin Records,

06:58.083 --> 07:00.017
goes to Miss Edna Buxton.

07:00.085 --> 07:02.747
Let's give her a big hand,
ladies and gentlemen.

07:02.821 --> 07:04.755
- Congratulations.

07:04.823 --> 07:07.257
-  ♪ How can I reach you ♪

07:07.325 --> 07:09.418
♪ When you're living ♪

07:10.729 --> 07:11.906
- ♪ In another world ♪
-  What are you
going to be singing?

07:11.930 --> 07:15.525
-  I'm going
to sing "In Another World."
- Who wrote it?

07:15.600 --> 07:18.967
- I did.
- Oh, okay.
Go ahead, any time.

07:25.377 --> 07:29.211
♪ If I could just tell you ♪

07:29.281 --> 07:32.478
♪ How my poor heart ♪

07:32.550 --> 07:35.815
♪ Is breaking ♪

07:37.522 --> 07:40.821
♪ Maybe you'd think twice ♪

07:40.892 --> 07:43.292
♪ 'Bout the road ♪

07:43.361 --> 07:47.661
♪ That you're taking ♪

07:47.732 --> 07:51.828
♪ Maybe you would look back ♪

07:54.572 --> 07:57.837
♪ And change your mind ♪

08:00.145 --> 08:03.342
♪ Maybe you would remember ♪

08:05.750 --> 08:09.516
♪ Love you left behind ♪

08:11.923 --> 08:15.359
♪ All I have is the memory ♪

08:17.529 --> 08:21.363
♪ Of when I was your girl ♪

08:24.002 --> 08:27.199
♪ How can I reach you ♪

08:27.272 --> 08:33.039
♪ When you're living
in another world ♪

08:33.111 --> 08:38.606
♪ When you're living
in another world ♪

08:40.217 --> 08:44.314
♪ Living in another world ♪ ♪

08:46.124 --> 08:49.389
Yeah, um...

08:49.461 --> 08:51.395
Thank you.
Uh, come on in.

08:52.964 --> 08:56.195
Nice...
Nice, uh, voice.

08:56.267 --> 09:00.397
- Thank you.
- But the thing of it is, toots,
we already have someone...

09:00.472 --> 09:03.305
- Someone just like me.
- Just like you.

09:03.375 --> 09:06.139
-  Excuse me.

09:06.211 --> 09:08.270
- Sit on the, uh...
- I'm sorry.

09:08.346 --> 09:11.713
- Do you want, uh...
- That's my only copy.

09:11.783 --> 09:14.718
- Wait, it's ruining my song!

09:14.786 --> 09:17.346
- Sit, sit, sit, sit.

09:17.422 --> 09:19.617
- Boy, you've been at this awhile, huh?
- I'm sorry.

09:19.691 --> 09:23.684
It's just that, you know,
I came here 11 months ago.

09:23.762 --> 09:26.697
Supposed to be
this big recording contract.

09:26.765 --> 09:29.928
And I won this prize.
Just all a big publicity stunt.

09:30.001 --> 09:33.095
Bunch of rats. Was it...
It was McMartin, right?

09:33.171 --> 09:35.639
Yeah, it was.
It was McMartin.

09:35.707 --> 09:38.540
And now I've been pounding
the pavement ever since,

09:38.610 --> 09:42.273
only to be told that you just
already have someone like me.

09:42.347 --> 09:44.907
You want me to, uh,
really burst your bubble?

09:44.983 --> 09:46.917
Oh, sure. Go ahead.

09:46.985 --> 09:49.317
You know, start bursting.

09:49.387 --> 09:54.120
Well, not only do we all
already have someone like you,

09:54.192 --> 09:56.956
but we all
are trying to get rid...

09:57.028 --> 09:59.462
of the someones like you
we already have.

09:59.531 --> 10:02.193
- Yeah, well.

10:02.267 --> 10:06.135
See, the thing of it is, toots, the
Patti Page/Peggy Lee days, they're over.

10:06.204 --> 10:09.139
- Yeah.
- Lady singers, they just don't sell.

10:09.207 --> 10:11.675
Male vocal groups,
that's the ticket these days.

10:11.743 --> 10:13.938
Yeah. You know,
I wrote it.

10:14.012 --> 10:16.537
- It's very nicely written.
It, uh, really is.
- Thank you.

10:16.614 --> 10:18.912
- Okay, I guess I'll just...
- Okay?

10:18.983 --> 10:22.350
Take my burst bubble
and just-just... I don't know.

10:22.420 --> 10:24.911
- Sorry about that.
- No, that's...

10:24.989 --> 10:26.923
- You know, wait a second.

10:26.991 --> 10:29.425
Lemme-Lemme-Lemme
hold onto this.

10:29.494 --> 10:31.519
- L-I have a stupid idea.
- Really?

10:31.596 --> 10:34.690
Yeah. D-Don't hold
your breath or anything.

10:34.766 --> 10:37.360
- L-I'll just see what I can do.
- Really?

10:37.435 --> 10:39.426
- Yes.
- Thank you.

10:39.504 --> 10:41.438
- Thank you.
- Very nice.

10:41.506 --> 10:44.441
- Well, yeah.
-  Thank you.

10:44.509 --> 10:47.376
- There's really no need
to cry anymore, okay?
- Okay. All right.

10:48.246 --> 10:50.510
- I'm sorry. Good-bye.
- All right.

10:50.582 --> 10:53.517
♪ ♪

11:02.293 --> 11:06.491
♪ Oh, the Blues ain't nothin' ♪

11:07.665 --> 11:12.728
♪ But a woman
cryin' for her man ♪

11:16.641 --> 11:20.236
♪ I said
the Blues ain't nothin' ♪

11:22.113 --> 11:25.571
♪ But a woman
lovin' a married man ♪

11:25.650 --> 11:27.584
Excuse me, miss.

11:27.652 --> 11:31.110
♪ Lord, Lord, Lord ♪

11:31.189 --> 11:33.783
♪ The Blues ain't nothin' ♪

11:36.961 --> 11:40.863
♪ But a common
low-down heart disease ♪

11:40.932 --> 11:42.866
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

11:44.269 --> 11:48.865
♪ Try to keep your man happy ♪

11:48.940 --> 11:55.539
♪ Although you find him
real hard to please ♪

11:55.613 --> 12:01.483
♪ Oh, yeah ♪ ♪

12:05.990 --> 12:10.484
- Hey.
- Oh, my God, it's...

12:10.562 --> 12:12.587
- ♪ Hey there ♪♪
- Yeah.

12:12.664 --> 12:16.293
Hi, hi!
I tried to return the dress.

12:16.367 --> 12:19.097
Oh... No, it looks good.
It looks good.

12:19.170 --> 12:21.604
How's that big
recordin' career goin'?

12:21.673 --> 12:25.268
Oh, it's really... Well, it's
not too swingin', actually.

12:25.343 --> 12:29.473
Oh, I'm Doris Shelley.
This is Betty, and this is Sha Sha.

12:29.547 --> 12:32.812
Hi, I'm Edna. You guys are swell.
You were really, really swell.

12:32.884 --> 12:36.115
- Stop it.
- Um,

12:36.187 --> 12:38.121
well, I just better go.

12:38.189 --> 12:41.022
Oh, Edna, come back.
We play Tuesday through Friday.

12:41.092 --> 12:43.253
Weekends are reserved for him.

12:43.328 --> 12:46.695
Gotcha.

13:02.180 --> 13:04.114
Edna?

13:04.182 --> 13:06.514
Oh. Joel Millner.

13:06.584 --> 13:09.883
I been lookin' for you for months. Okay,
all weekend. You don't have a phone?

13:09.954 --> 13:12.286
- No.
- Why don't you have a phone?
You gotta have a phone.

13:12.357 --> 13:15.952
You can't make it in this business
without a phone. What are you drinking?

13:16.027 --> 13:18.222
- A vanilla coke.
- That's disgusting.

13:18.296 --> 13:20.355
Are you eating?
I'm buying.

13:20.431 --> 13:23.127
Can we get service here?
We been waiting 20 minutes.

13:23.201 --> 13:25.135
Hold on a sec.
I'm busy.

13:25.203 --> 13:29.469
She'll have a grilled cheese
and tomato and onion rings.
I'll have a cheeseburger combo.

13:31.309 --> 13:34.870
- Anyway, so your demo. That's the one.
- Yes. "In Another World."

13:34.946 --> 13:38.848
- Nice voice. Great song.
- Thank you. I wrote it.

13:38.916 --> 13:40.850
I know you did.
It was funny.

13:40.918 --> 13:44.752
When I listened to it,
I thought how nuts it was...

13:44.822 --> 13:48.519
for a gal to be singing
such strong material.

13:48.593 --> 13:51.528
- Oh, I'm unfeminine now too.
- And that's what I like.

13:51.596 --> 13:53.621
- Only...
- Only you have someone like me.

13:53.698 --> 13:56.058
No, I don't think there's
another one like you in the world.

13:56.100 --> 13:59.433
I manage a male vocal group
called The Stylettes. You heard of them?

13:59.504 --> 14:02.200
- Yeah, sure. Yeah. Yeah.
- Yes? Yes? Good.

14:02.273 --> 14:05.436
This song is perfect for their voices.
We could all make money.

14:05.510 --> 14:10.243
- I bet you have other songs too.
- No, I'm planning
to record my own songs.

14:10.314 --> 14:13.545
What do you mean? You're either
a singer or songwriter. Which is it?

14:13.618 --> 14:16.416
- I'm both.
- Nobody's both.
You're either one or the other.

14:16.487 --> 14:18.421
Well, I'm both.

14:22.994 --> 14:26.395
The day will come again
when girl singers are top of the heap.

14:26.464 --> 14:30.366
'Til the timing's right,
why not make a little money
writing songs for other people?

14:30.435 --> 14:34.166
- You want me to sell my songs to you?
- Let me prove it.

14:34.238 --> 14:36.172
I'll book a studio, right?

14:36.240 --> 14:38.640
You can meet the fellas,
listen to them sing your song.

14:38.710 --> 14:42.168
If you don't like it,
I won't bug you again.

14:42.246 --> 14:45.841
Trust me. I'm Joel Millner.
I'm a nice Hebrew boy.

14:45.917 --> 14:49.182
- Actually, my mother's Italian.
I'm from New Jersey.

14:49.253 --> 14:51.312
- Can I be perfectly honest?
- Hmm?

14:51.389 --> 14:53.857
You gotta change your name.

14:53.925 --> 14:56.450
Edna Buxton. That's the worst
name I ever heard in my life.

14:56.527 --> 14:58.739
Where are you from that would curse you
with a name like that?

14:58.763 --> 15:01.630
- Philadelphia.
- Oh, ouch. Keeps getting worse.

15:01.699 --> 15:04.793
Wait a minute.
The Buxtons of Philadelphia?

15:04.869 --> 15:08.896
- Not Buxton Steel?
- Mm-hmm.

15:10.942 --> 15:14.400
- We gotta do a little reinvention.
- Oh.

15:14.479 --> 15:17.710
♪ Ooh, we, ooh ♪

15:17.782 --> 15:20.546
♪ Ooh, we, ooh ♪

15:20.618 --> 15:24.247
- Psst!
- ♪ Ooh, we, ooh ♪ ♪

15:25.623 --> 15:27.557
- Hey, kiddo.
- Hi, Joel.

15:27.625 --> 15:29.889
- Come on in. Good to see you.
- Sure, sure.

15:29.961 --> 15:33.522
Fellas, this is the young lady
who wrote your next hit.

15:33.598 --> 15:37.125
I want to introduce
you all to... Denise Waverly.

15:37.201 --> 15:39.328
Denise Waverly
from South Philly.

15:39.403 --> 15:41.337
- You ever been to South Philly?
- No.

15:41.405 --> 15:44.431
- She's an original. To rise outta
those slums, lemme tell you.
- Y-yeah.

15:44.509 --> 15:47.876
- Denise... Waverly. Hi.
- Walter. Pleasure to meet you.

15:47.945 --> 15:49.879
- Full service. Get your coat?

15:49.947 --> 15:53.474
- I'm the maitre d'.
- Denise Waverly?
What's it all about, Joel?

15:53.551 --> 15:57.180
- ♪ Ooh ♪
- ♪ All I have
is the memory ♪

15:57.255 --> 16:00.884
- ♪ Ooh ♪
- ♪ When you were
my girl ♪ ♪

16:00.958 --> 16:03.358
- Come on, man.
- Get him a lyric sheet,
somebody. Come on.

16:03.427 --> 16:05.361
I know the lyrics.
That's just it.

16:05.429 --> 16:07.674
- I know the lyrics.
- You know them?
I don't hear you knowin' 'em.

16:07.698 --> 16:10.030
- I apologize, Miss Waverly.

16:10.101 --> 16:13.366
What you wrote here, being in love
with someone you can't have,

16:13.437 --> 16:16.565
and you let 'em go
and have their own life... beautiful.

16:16.641 --> 16:19.007
It's something that
happened to me before.

16:19.076 --> 16:22.512
I know how personal it must be.
I don't want to invade your privacy.

16:22.580 --> 16:26.038
- I just want to do the song righteous.

16:26.117 --> 16:29.883
Uh, geez. I don't need
to hear any more, Joel.

16:29.954 --> 16:31.922
Listen, the song is yours, guys.

16:31.989 --> 16:34.082
It's never happened
to me anyway.

16:34.158 --> 16:37.889
I just made it up to pass
the night away, you know.

16:37.962 --> 16:40.988
- Denise, we need a B-side.
What else you got?
- B-side?

16:41.065 --> 16:44.228
Well, you know, I sort of write
for girls like myself.

16:44.302 --> 16:46.770
-  We need somethin' upbeat.
- Upbeat?

16:46.838 --> 16:49.329
Up-tempo? Okay.
Something... Hmm.

16:49.407 --> 16:53.366
Something new for me, but okay.
Let's see what I can do.

16:53.978 --> 16:56.071
- You get the same percentage as me.
- Okay.

16:56.147 --> 16:58.809
But this is only until I can
record my own stuff, right?

16:58.883 --> 17:01.562
- When I make my own record...
- Absolutely, when the time is right.

17:01.586 --> 17:03.520
Read it before you sign it.

17:03.588 --> 17:06.021
Toots, my new
receptionist, Judy.

17:06.089 --> 17:08.023
- Hi.
- Hello.

17:08.092 --> 17:10.185
Now I want you to worry about
writing the songs.

17:10.261 --> 17:13.195
I want personal ones
like "In Another World."

17:13.263 --> 17:16.700
Now I am worried. What if I can't
just think up another one like that?

17:16.767 --> 17:19.031
Keep your eyes and ears open.
Everyone is in pain.

17:19.103 --> 17:21.367
Come on. I want
to show you your office.

17:25.276 --> 17:29.042
You got a piano,
nice frosted glass, window, view.

17:29.113 --> 17:31.547
Huh? You got a roof.

17:31.616 --> 17:34.050
You put a plant here,
it's like you're in the country.

17:34.118 --> 17:36.814
Okay, look at this. You could
pace back and forth if you're a pacer.

17:36.888 --> 17:39.823
Hey, Monte!
How ya doin'?

17:39.891 --> 17:42.155
You hear the sound?
You can hear airplanes, everything.

17:42.226 --> 17:45.161
Good vocal sound.
You're frustrated? You schmuck!

17:46.230 --> 17:48.596
- You don't like it?
- No, I like it.

17:48.666 --> 17:51.328
- You don't like it.
- I like it. It's...

17:51.402 --> 17:53.836
Well, I write songs
in the bedroom...

17:53.905 --> 17:56.499
or in the bathtub
or on the fire escape.

17:56.574 --> 17:59.008
That won't do, Denise.
You're a professional now.

17:59.076 --> 18:01.010
I'm gonna let you in
on a secret.

18:01.078 --> 18:04.172
This is where all the hits
are gonna be made from now on.

18:04.248 --> 18:07.513
Right here. One scene,
all happening under one roof.

18:07.585 --> 18:10.679
If you have your artists,
your songwriters, lead sheets office,

18:10.755 --> 18:13.690
recording studio, studio musicians,
all in the same building,

18:13.758 --> 18:16.090
you can have
a new hit record every week.

18:16.160 --> 18:19.687
- Thanks, Roberta. See you tomorrow.

18:19.764 --> 18:22.198
Hey, can I listen
to that for a sec?

18:22.266 --> 18:25.702
- Come on, come on. Just for a sec.
- ♪ How my heart is breaking ♪

18:25.770 --> 18:28.364
Oh, my God,
it's "In Another World."

18:28.439 --> 18:31.636
- Lady, can I listen to the song now?
- Why don't you buy the record?

18:31.709 --> 18:34.644
Why don't you go buy it, lady,
if you can find it.

18:34.712 --> 18:38.978
- I bought the last copy
at the record store.
- You're kidding.

18:39.050 --> 18:41.416
