I was wondering, is it because of your
working class background...

34:29.466 --> 34:33.766
that you feel free to examine these
very real, honest themes in your music?

34:36.739 --> 34:41.938
Um... I can assure you my background
doesn't have anything to do with it.

34:43.580 --> 34:47.311
I'm curious. You had a big hit last year
with "In Another World"...

34:47.384 --> 34:49.614
that you wrote by yourself.

34:49.686 --> 34:52.280
I was curious why you
decided to collaborate.

34:52.355 --> 34:55.255
We met and hit it off,
decided to work together.

34:55.324 --> 34:57.020
Denise?

34:58.595 --> 35:02.531
Well, I guess what he's
saying is basically true.

35:02.599 --> 35:06.535
- Joel actually...
- Joel Millner introduced
us at Fernando's Blue Room up in Harlem.

35:06.603 --> 35:08.867
He's the man that we blame.

35:08.939 --> 35:10.964
Is it a marriage made in heaven?

35:11.041 --> 35:15.034
No! We're not... married.
We're partners. We're not married.

35:15.111 --> 35:18.774
I'm here right now with Denise Waverly
and Howard Caszatt...

35:18.848 --> 35:24.115
who have written a very controversial
new song by the Luminaries.

35:24.187 --> 35:26.417
- "Unwanted Number."
- "Unwanted Number."

35:26.489 --> 35:28.821
- Available now.
- Thank you, Howard.

35:28.892 --> 35:32.487
Voss-Beat Records. We certainly
are going to keep playing it here.

35:32.562 --> 35:35.395
- Thank you, John.
- ♪♪

35:35.465 --> 35:38.730
- Wasn't l... I thought I was terrible.
- You were wonderful.

35:38.802 --> 35:41.066
You were great, honey.
You were terrific.

35:41.137 --> 35:45.096
I thought you were very
honest and straightforward
with everything you said.

35:45.175 --> 35:47.871
- Oh, thank you. You helped.
- ♪♪

35:47.944 --> 35:50.845
- Can we take these off?
- No, take 'em with you.

35:53.750 --> 35:56.480
-  Because I'm not gonna do it.
- Hi.

35:56.553 --> 36:00.216
- Okay?
- Could I just give this to, uh...

36:00.290 --> 36:03.487
- I'm not gonna say that.
- John? Yeah.

36:03.560 --> 36:07.496
- What?
- Miss Waverly just dropped this by.

36:07.564 --> 36:09.088
I'll call you back.

36:09.165 --> 36:12.259
Denise! Hi.
So glad I caught you.

36:12.335 --> 36:15.463
I didn't mean to drag you
from your work.

36:15.538 --> 36:18.336
No, I can't think of
a more delightful way...

36:18.408 --> 36:22.276
- To avoid a confrontation
with one of my writers.
- Ah!

36:22.345 --> 36:26.281
- So what is this?
- Well, it's a toaster.
What do you think?

36:26.349 --> 36:29.284
- No, it's... Pretty obvious.

36:29.352 --> 36:33.448
Got these... I just wanted to thank you
for having us on the show.

36:33.523 --> 36:36.390
This is amazing. I've been looking
for these for years.

36:36.459 --> 36:40.156
I heard you say it on your show,
and I happened to be in the Village...

36:40.230 --> 36:44.394
in this thrift shop, and I saw them,
so I got them for you.

36:44.467 --> 36:46.799
- You like them?
- Thank you so much.

36:48.705 --> 36:53.574
Well, l... I should get back.
Can't avoid this forever.

36:53.643 --> 36:56.043
Oh.

36:56.112 --> 36:58.103
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

36:58.181 --> 37:01.309
- Howard?
- Hmm.

37:01.384 --> 37:03.944
We should write a wedding song.

37:04.020 --> 37:06.921
What's the social angle?

37:06.990 --> 37:11.120
Oh, well, I wasn't thinking about that.
That's your department.

37:11.194 --> 37:13.628
I don't believe in marriage.

37:15.765 --> 37:20.168
What do you mean you don't believe
in marriage? You're joking, right?

37:20.236 --> 37:22.761
No. Why?

37:22.839 --> 37:25.501
Oh, God. Come on.
You believe in it?

37:25.575 --> 37:27.770
Marriage is
a bourgeois convention...

37:27.844 --> 37:31.712
You honestly think a contract can
or should bind people to each other?

37:31.781 --> 37:34.760
Why should modern affairs
between men and women be
modeled on an arrangement...

37:34.784 --> 37:38.049
that was forced on people by the
church and state during feudal times?

37:38.121 --> 37:42.558
Even then, it didn't work. Men were
bringing home syphilis to their wives.

37:45.562 --> 37:49.157
- Well... I mean, I just
think that, you know,
- Hmm?

37:49.232 --> 37:51.962
People taking vows
in front of other people...

37:52.035 --> 37:54.299
- What?
- It's kind of beautiful.

37:54.370 --> 37:56.930
I think that kind of
romanticism bullshit's...

37:57.006 --> 37:59.907
what keeps people in bondage.

38:01.945 --> 38:05.244
Your friend John Murray's married.
He's not conservative.

38:07.183 --> 38:10.084
- But... John Murray?
- Mm-hmm.

38:10.153 --> 38:13.520
What... What is this... You have
a crush on this guy or something?

38:13.590 --> 38:15.615
- No.
- Huh?

38:15.692 --> 38:17.956
- You do. Look at you.
-  Do not!

38:18.027 --> 38:20.757
Forget about him, all right?
You're mine.

38:20.830 --> 38:24.960
- Am I?
- ♪ I know, girl
you were runnin' round ♪

38:25.034 --> 38:27.662
♪ ♪

38:30.640 --> 38:33.234
- ♪♪
- You married him?

38:33.309 --> 38:35.869
- You told me to sign here, right?

38:35.945 --> 38:37.879
- Just sign here.
- Joel, listen...

38:37.947 --> 38:40.643
- I'd like you to meet...
- I know, the new receptionist.

38:40.717 --> 38:44.619
Oh, golly, no. This lady here
is a new member...

38:44.687 --> 38:47.383
of the Charny Music family.

38:47.457 --> 38:49.391
I just signed
Cheryl and her partner.

38:49.459 --> 38:53.452
First song they've written
is gonna be the Luminaries' next hit.

38:53.530 --> 38:55.589
Oh, that's great!
That's great.

38:55.665 --> 38:58.429
- Thanks.
- They could use a hit.

38:58.501 --> 39:01.902
The last three songs we wrote for them
were banned from the radios.

39:01.971 --> 39:06.374
It's funny, because in Europe
such bannings are never heard of.

39:06.442 --> 39:10.242
- Really?
- I guess it's 'cause
we're far more freethinking.

39:10.313 --> 39:13.612
- Yeah.
- Denise Waverly.

39:13.683 --> 39:16.584
Cheryl Steed. Hi.

39:16.653 --> 39:20.783
Well, if you need anything,
my office is just down the hall.

39:20.857 --> 39:24.258
Thank you, and mine
is just next door,

39:24.327 --> 39:27.057
- If you need me for anything.

39:27.130 --> 39:29.223
-  What?
- Uh, next door?

39:29.299 --> 39:33.201
The front of the building.
You have windows. That's nice.

39:33.269 --> 39:36.102
L... I insisted.
This place is so dreary.

39:36.172 --> 39:38.106
- Mm, yeah.
- Hello.

39:38.174 --> 39:39.698
Hi.

39:39.776 --> 39:42.040
- Howard, honey,
- Hmm?

39:42.111 --> 39:44.204
This is Cheryl,

39:44.280 --> 39:46.561
- And she's part of
the Charny Music family now.
- Charmed.

39:46.616 --> 39:50.108
- Welcome.
- So just think of her like a sister.

39:50.186 --> 39:53.553
Howard is my writing partner,
and he's also my boyfriend.

39:53.623 --> 39:55.716
- Oh.
- Who's your partner?

39:55.792 --> 39:59.159
Uh, Matthew.
He... He's my husband.

39:59.229 --> 40:02.687
Oh! That's great.
Isn't that great?

40:03.833 --> 40:05.801
- Oops!
- Oops.

40:05.868 --> 40:07.563
Hmm.

40:07.637 --> 40:09.628
- Joel will be next door.
- I'm just lookin'.

40:09.706 --> 40:12.402
- Miss, uh, Waverly.
- Yeah. Welcome aboard.

40:12.475 --> 40:14.500
Howard.

40:14.577 --> 40:16.636
- Adieu.
- Adieu.

40:18.314 --> 40:22.512
- Whew! She's got
the cutest little... accent.
- I'll "adieu" you.

40:22.585 --> 40:24.610
She's from Europe.

40:27.156 --> 40:29.624
All I know is I'm gettin' hot.

40:29.692 --> 40:32.525
Cheryl, your husband's
20 minutes late!

40:32.595 --> 40:36.122
I know. But I called and they said
he's on his way. I think we should wait.

40:36.199 --> 40:39.498
- Where is he?
- We have to wait for Matthew.
I can't start without him.

40:39.569 --> 40:42.299
- Time is money and money
is time. Let's go.
- Come on, Joel.

40:42.372 --> 40:44.772
I'm not waiting
any longer. Sorry.

40:44.841 --> 40:47.605
- Let's put one down.

40:47.677 --> 40:51.477
- I can't afford it.
- Okay, fine, but you're
laying it on a bit thick.

40:54.317 --> 40:58.845
- Make sure the vocal is up high
so we can really hear the lyric.
- Yeah, I understand.

40:58.921 --> 41:01.617
♪ Well, I met you in December ♪

41:01.691 --> 41:04.683
♪ Underneath a winter's sky ♪

41:04.761 --> 41:09.289
♪ I could tell
by the kissing
on New Year's ♪

41:09.365 --> 41:13.199
♪ You were gonna be my guy ♪

41:13.269 --> 41:17.262
- ♪ February, tapped me
on the shoulder ♪
- ♪ Tap, tap ♪

41:17.340 --> 41:21.208
♪ Turned around
and whispered in my ear ♪

41:21.277 --> 41:24.974
Decided to come, did you?
We've been waiting two hours for you.

41:25.048 --> 41:28.449
Joel's been looking at his watch.
The girls have been hanging around.

41:28.518 --> 41:32.852
- Costs a fortune to keep studio time
when people are hanging around.
- Get off my back.

41:32.922 --> 41:38.383
- ♪ I do for you ♪
- Where were you?

41:38.461 --> 41:42.295
I'm here now, okay?
Let's go to work.

41:42.365 --> 41:45.163
- We are working, Matthew.
- ♪ And now it's June ♪

41:45.234 --> 41:49.068
♪ And we're gonna get married
the day you say ♪

41:49.138 --> 41:52.073
♪ That I'm the one ♪

41:52.141 --> 41:55.042
- ♪ Ooo ♪
- ♪ Do you make a promise that
we'll always be together ♪

41:55.111 --> 41:57.011
- ♪ I do ♪
- ♪ I do ♪

41:57.080 --> 42:00.743
Denise, what do you think?

42:00.817 --> 42:04.344
I think it's a sure hit,
Joel. Congratulations.

42:04.420 --> 42:07.150
- ♪ I do ♪
- Excuse me.

42:07.223 --> 42:10.920
- ♪ Do you make a promise that
we'll always be together ♪
- Cheryl.

42:10.993 --> 42:14.929
- ♪ I do, I do ♪
- Thanks.

42:14.997 --> 42:18.524
♪ Do you make a promise that
our love'll last forever ♪

42:18.601 --> 42:20.535
- ♪ I do ♪
- ♪ I do ♪

42:21.637 --> 42:23.127
- ♪ Do you ♪
- ♪ I do ♪

42:23.206 --> 42:28.200
- ♪ Do you make a promise that
we'll always be together ♪ ♪

42:28.277 --> 42:33.305
Okay, so I'm a boob. You
should've written that wedding
song. "I Do" is number four.

42:35.017 --> 42:38.453
- Howard?
- Hmm?

42:38.521 --> 42:42.719
You're not gonna believe this,
but, um... I think I'm pregnant.

42:42.792 --> 42:45.386
No, you can't be.
I pulled out.

42:45.461 --> 42:49.261
I went to the doctor today and, um...
Well, he's pretty sure that I am.

42:49.332 --> 42:52.859
I just have to wait
and see if the rabbit dies.

42:52.935 --> 42:56.393
- How long does that take?
- About a week.

42:56.472 --> 42:59.202
Oh, shit.

43:00.810 --> 43:02.744
- There is something else.
- What?

43:02.812 --> 43:05.576
My name isn't...
Well, it isn't really Denise.

43:05.648 --> 43:07.878
It's...

43:07.950 --> 43:12.250
It... It's Edna.
Edna Buxton. Buxton Steel.

43:12.321 --> 43:14.721
- That's my family's business.
- You putting me on?

43:14.791 --> 43:18.750
You see, Joel invented the whole name
and the working class persona,

43:18.828 --> 43:21.273
and I didn't know how to tell you
'cause you'd be disappointed.

43:21.297 --> 43:24.323
Let me get this straight. You're
telling me that you're an heiress?

43:24.400 --> 43:26.493
- Yeah.
- You're an heiress?

43:26.569 --> 43:28.503
- Yeah.
- You're an heiress?

43:28.571 --> 43:31.005
- Yeah.
- You don't look like an heiress.

43:31.073 --> 43:35.271
That's nice. What's an heiress
supposed to look like?

43:35.344 --> 43:40.839
Grace Kelly. That's funny. That's the
sort of woman I thought I'd end up with.

43:40.917 --> 43:45.286
Someone with that kind of grace.
When we'd hit it off, it'd surprise me.

43:45.354 --> 43:48.346
I thought my dream girl
would be blond, coy.

43:48.424 --> 43:51.120
- Howard!
- Oh.

43:51.194 --> 43:54.960
- That's a terrible thing to say!
- Honey, listen. I'm sorry.

43:55.031 --> 43:59.161
It's just I'm scared, that's all.
We don't have any money right now.

43:59.235 --> 44:03.035
- If you have a baby, you're
not gonna be able to work.
- Yes, I can!

44:03.105 --> 44:05.403
I can take the baby
to work with us.

44:05.475 --> 44:08.808
Oh, yeah. The Brill Building.
That's a great place to bring up a kid.

44:08.878 --> 44:11.847
It's not a bad place.

44:15.551 --> 44:20.079
What... What the hell's your name again?
Ethel? Effie? Alberta?

44:20.156 --> 44:22.283
- It's Edna.
- Buxom?

44:22.358 --> 44:26.454
- Edna Buxton. It's a fine name.
- Buxton? Well.

44:26.529 --> 44:31.262
- Thank God the kid's gonna
have my name at least, huh?
- Caszatt. That's terrible.

44:31.334 --> 44:34.132
Songwriters Denise Waverly
and Howard Caszatt...

44:34.203 --> 44:38.367
were married in a 15-minute
civil ceremony in New York this weekend.

44:38.441 --> 44:41.035
The couple are expecting
a child in October.

44:41.110 --> 44:47.674
♪ You're hanging on
to dreams that
will never come true ♪ ♪

44:47.750 --> 44:50.514
Hey, guys.
That was really terrific.

44:50.586 --> 44:55.148
Um, on the bridge, when you get to the
"kid", you're cutting it off a little.

44:55.224 --> 44:58.318
- Stretch it out.
Stretch "kid" out, guys.
- You can just...

44:58.394 --> 45:01.886
Let it really come
to a natural ending, okay?

45:01.964 --> 45:05.058
- Why don't you sit down?
You have my son in there.
- Okay. All right, sweetie.

45:05.134 --> 45:09.537
- Let's make hit records. Let's start.
- ♪ Heartbreak kid ♪

45:11.307 --> 45:15.209
♪ King of sorrow ♪

45:16.445 --> 45:19.676
♪ Blue today ♪

45:20.917 --> 45:25.251
♪ Bluer tomorrow ♪

45:25.321 --> 45:28.552
♪ It's all up to you ♪

45:28.624 --> 45:35.621
♪ What will you do
Heartbreak kid ♪

45:35.698 --> 45:37.632
That's a damn good song, doll.

45:37.700 --> 45:41.727
Keep this gal knocked up and
she'll make you a millionaire.
This is gonna be a hit.

45:41.804 --> 45:43.738
- What?
- Her first since...

45:43.806 --> 45:46.969
- Since she started
writing with me, huh?
- I didn't say that.

45:47.043 --> 45:49.170
- Could you guys...
- I'll see you at home.

45:49.245 --> 45:51.509
Howard, you can't just leave
during my session.

45:51.581 --> 45:54.141
For God's sake, Denise,
concentrate on your work!

45:54.216 --> 45:57.208
- Joel, Jesus, your tact
doesn't exactly help.
- My tact?

45:57.286 --> 46:00.551
You blame it on me that
your husband is jealous of your talent!

46:00.623 --> 46:05.583
He's not jealous. I mean,
I'm getting really fed up with the way...

46:05.661 --> 46:08.562
- Oh! Howard!

46:08.631 --> 46:10.656
- My water is breaking.
- What's happening?

46:10.733 --> 46:14.294
- Cheryl, my water's breaking.
Get Howard!
- L, uh... I'm gonna be sick.

46:14.370 --> 46:16.429
- Get Howard!
-  What's happening?

46:16.505 --> 46:20.271
- I'm having a baby, Joel.
Please, get Howard.
- Dagmar!

46:20.343 --> 46:23.437
- Howard!
-  Everybody out!

46:23.512 --> 46:27.676
It's not an epidemic. I'm having a baby.
It is a perfectly natural...

46:27.750 --> 46:29.895
- We gotta get you to the hospital.
- Guys, I'm really sorry.

46:29.919 --> 46:31.944
- I'll get Howard.
- Guys, I'm sorry.

46:32.021 --> 46:34.785
- We gotta get you to the hospital.

46:34.857 --> 46:37.849
Geez, I know.
I know the... Cheryl.

46:37.927 --> 46:42.489
Oh, God. What did I do here?

46:44.333 --> 46:46.801
- What happened?

46:46.869 --> 46:49.838
- I'm gonna have a baby.
- Now?

46:49.905 --> 46:52.567
- Yeah.
- Oh, God! Come on.

46:52.642 --> 46:55.110
- Okay. It's okay.
- Just do it like this.

46:55.177 --> 46:57.702
I'll wheel you out.
It's okay.

46:57.780 --> 47:00.647
♪ ♪

47:00.716 --> 47:03.116
♪ He was the one ♪

47:03.185 --> 47:08.418
♪ Second to none in your eyes ♪

47:09.558 --> 47:12.652
- ♪ But you couldn't see ♪

47:12.728 --> 47:16.425
- ♪ What's turned out to be
a disguise ♪
- Oh, come on. She's asleep.

47:18.167 --> 47:20.829
- Sweet darling.
- She's asleep.

47:20.903 --> 47:22.894
- ♪ She led you on ♪
-  Okay.

47:22.972 --> 47:27.068
♪ She had you fooled
from the start ♪

47:28.811 --> 47:32.338
- ♪ And though she's long gone ♪

47:32.415 --> 47:37.478
♪ Boy, you're still
playing the part ♪

47:37.553 --> 47:39.987
- Oooh!

47:40.056 --> 47:43.048
- ♪ Heartbreak kid ♪
- That's okay.

47:43.125 --> 47:45.085
- ♪ King of sorrows ♪♪
- Luma's got a pretty face.

47:46.929 --> 47:50.922
This is where I work. And this is where
I come to work every day...

47:51.000 --> 47:54.026
and I write pretty,
pretty songs with your daddy.

47:54.103 --> 47:56.901
- ♪♪

47:56.972 --> 48:00.237
- Here's your Uncle Joel. You got her?
-  Yeah.

48:00.309 --> 48:03.472
Now that your collaboration
with... Caszatt...

48:03.546 --> 48:07.346
has taken a slightly
different direction,

48:07.416 --> 48:10.544
I started lookin' around
this place for a...

48:10.619 --> 48:15.750
Well, uh...
for an interesting, uh...

48:15.825 --> 48:20.592
Look. I thought
maybe you two gals...

48:20.663 --> 48:23.131
could try writing
a song together.

48:26.035 --> 48:29.027
- Cheryl writes with her husband.
- I write with Matthew.

48:29.105 --> 48:31.733
- How would Matthew feel?
- Matthew would be devastated.

48:31.807 --> 48:35.607
I understand, but I don't see
why Cheryl's talent should
be exclusive to her husband.

48:35.678 --> 48:39.444
- I'm sure she'd agree with you.
- There's a whole other set of problems.

48:39.515 --> 48:44.612
Whoa, whoa, take it easy.
I'm not asking... This is no
"Et tu, Brute?" business.

48:44.687 --> 48:46.951
There's no betrayal here.
It's an experiment.

48:47.022 --> 48:50.219
If you guys combine,
if you combust, we ignite, we go.

48:54.630 --> 48:57.497
Now the first assignment...

48:59.301 --> 49:03.431
is to come up with something
for Kelly Porter.

49:04.573 --> 49:06.507
Okay?

49:06.575 --> 49:08.941
- No, Joel. No.

49:09.011 --> 49:12.674
- Kelly Porter, the ingenue. No.
- Kelly Porter, yes.

49:12.748 --> 49:16.309
- "Dring Dring. Are you home?"
Kelly Porter?
- She ran out of hair spray.

49:16.385 --> 49:19.786
-  Here. Have it.
- She's home getting her hair done.

49:19.855 --> 49:21.755
I'm glad you're so enthusiastic.

49:21.824 --> 49:25.453
Well, I'm gonna split in
ten minutes because this is, you know...

49:25.528 --> 49:28.656
- Waiting here for how... how long now?
- Cheryl, patience, patience.

49:28.731 --> 49:30.995
- My God.
- Oh, look. Look.

49:36.839 --> 49:39.774
She seems upset.

49:46.348 --> 49:48.908
- Oh. Hi. Hi.
- Hi.

49:48.984 --> 49:51.544
Let me talk first
when she gets here.

49:51.620 --> 49:54.851
- Hi.
-  Hi.

49:54.924 --> 49:59.384
- Sorry we're late.
- Hi. Oh, I'm Marion.
I'm Kelly's roommate.

49:59.461 --> 50:02.555
- Marion. Denise. Uh, Cheryl.
- Cheryl Steed.

50:02.631 --> 50:06.067
Hi, I'm Kelly Porter.
So nice to meet both of you.

50:09.538 --> 50:12.234
Okay, so you have your meeting.

50:12.308 --> 50:15.573
I'll make your reservation.
Chinese.

50:15.644 --> 50:19.842
Yeah, that'll be swell.
Bye.

50:20.983 --> 50:22.917
So, uh...

50:22.985 --> 50:26.887
Gosh, I'm honored that
you'd consider writing a song for me.

50:26.956 --> 50:31.120
- Oh.
- I mean, people have, you know,
certain ideas about me...

50:31.193 --> 50:35.061
that are created by my publicist
and this TV show that I do.

50:35.130 --> 50:39.624
They really have no idea
who I am or what my life is like...

50:39.702 --> 50:41.795
or what I go through...

50:41.871 --> 50:46.001
with the person I love.

50:46.075 --> 50:47.872
Kelly.

